  "serviceNotes": {
    "engine oil": "Peugeot’s published EU maintenance programme for 208 (petrol/diesel ICE) uses periodic services at 20,000 km or 12 months (minor) with oil and filter replacement, matching Stellantis documentation summarised in official servicing guides.",
    "cabin filter": "Pollen filter is replaced at the scheduled maintenance interval (typically every 20,000 km / 12 months on the standard programme).",
    "air filter": "Air filter service is included at the same minor maintenance interval for ICE versions.",
    "fuel filter": "Diesel variants specify fuel filter on the major maintenance cycle; Stellantis schedules commonly place this near 40,000 km / 24 months—petrol cars have no separate fuel filter service.",
    "coolant flush": "Coolant should be renewed periodically; 120,000 km is a common preventive interval for small Stellantis turbo engines.",
    "wet belt inspection": "PureTech engines use a wet timing belt; specialist forums recommend inspection and planned belt service around 100,000 km to avoid debris-related failures—verify engine code (some are chain).",
    "brake fluid": "Peugeot specifies brake fluid replacement every 2 years as part of the scheduled maintenance programme.",
    "spark plugs": "Spark plug replacement at 40,000 km is specified in the Peugeot 208 maintenance schedule for petrol engines.",
    "check brake pads": "Brake system inspection is performed at each scheduled service visit."
  },
